Wensday , April 27th , 2016

					Journal

The essence of human / higher level learning is developing the skill to discriminate patterns
and identify shared characteristics across events (stimuli).
Memorization - the regurgitation of facts - is considered the lowest level of learning.
Why, then, are students encouraged to learn CS?
What should students learn from CS?
Reflection is required for this question. " I don't know " does not suffice. If in doubt, 
consult the syllabus.

Students are encouraged to take CS because it can teach them valuble life skills such
as computer programming, pattern recognition, and problem solving which can help
you in the future, and allow the student to make better life choices ,in general,
